<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-756-727  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 756 727.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  July 17 1989 n426 p1(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>RISC loyalties shifting. (reduced-instruction-set computers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Nee, Eric.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The volatility of the reduced-instruction-set computer (RISC)business has been underscored by the decision of Unisys Corp toshift from Sun Microsystems Inc's SPARC chip to Motorola's 88000.andO;The move catapulted Motorola's status in the RISC market which isdominated by Sun and Mips Computer Systems Inc. Intel Corp is alsoin the top four with its i860 microprocessor.andP;  The competitionamong the four companies is expected to increase because no oneclear industry standard is emerging.andP;  Computer vendors aretherefore expected to switch from one supplier to another.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Unisys Corp. (equipment and supplies)Motorola Inc. (products)Sun Microsystems Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    MOT; UIS; SUNW.andO;Topic:     CompetitionStandardizationMicroprocessorsReduced-Instruction-Set Computers.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   RISC takers. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>